verses.roman:
premāveśe paḍilā teṅho samudrera jale
tāṅre tumi uṭhāilā āpanāra jāle

synonyms: prema-āveśe—out of ecstatic emotion; paḍilā—fell down; teṅho—He; samudrera jale—in the water of the sea; tāṅre—Him; tumi—you; uṭhāilā—brought out; āpanāra jāle—in your net.
translation: "Because of ecstatic love, the Lord fell into the sea, and you have caught Him in your net and rescued Him.
